	     Durban – A 48-year-old motorist died after the bakkie he had been driving overturned in Umhlanga, north of Durban, on Wednesday, KwaZulu-Natal police said. Police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala told News24 that Durban North police were investigating a case of culpable homicide following the incident. She said the accident occurred at about 13:00. "It is alleged ... a Hyundai bakkie overturned in Umhlanga. A 48-year-old driver died at the scene, while three passengers were taken to hospital for medical examination."  The cause of the accident is still unknown, Gwala added. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  